for
you
to offend
me;
and I'm sure the young fellow is quite
welcome to both my names, if you wish him to have 'em.
And I merely meant, Miss Mildred, resumed Tom, who
feared he might have gone too far; that the young
gentleman
quite
without any fault of his ownis probably
ignorant
how he came by two names that have so long pertained
